## Brainstorm — emergent coordination via shared environment
## Multiple ideators contribute to a shared idea board, then a curator selects the best.

### Start a brainstorm session (spawns ideator agents)
POST http://localhost:9000/brainstorm
Content-Type: application/json

{"topic": "Innovative ways to reduce food waste in urban restaurants", "numIdeators": 3}

### Check the idea board (replace boardId from above)
GET http://localhost:9000/brainstorm/{{boardId}}/board

### Trigger curation (after ideators finish — check board to see ideator status)
POST http://localhost:9000/brainstorm/{{boardId}}/curate

### Check curator result (replace taskId from curate response)
GET http://localhost:9000/brainstorm/task/{{taskId}}

### Check individual ideator task (replace taskId from start response)
GET http://localhost:9000/brainstorm/task/{{taskId}}
